## 5. Responsive Strategy

### 5.1 Breakpoint Implementation

| Breakpoint | Container | Card Grid | Layout | Navigation |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `< sm` (default) | Full width, px-4 | 1 col | Stacked | Hamburger |
| `sm` (640px+) | px-6 | 2 col | Stacked | Hamburger |
| `md` (768px+) | px-6 | 2 col | Side-by-side forms | Hamburger |
| `lg` (1024px+) | max-w-7xl, px-6 | 3 col | Multi-column | Full nav |

### 5.2 Mobile-Specific UX

1. **Pull-to-refresh**: For list pages (Assignments, Exams, Grades)
2. **Bottom sticky action bar**: On exam pages — action buttons sticky at bottom
3. **Swipe to reveal**: On notification items (swipe to mark read / delete)
4. **FAB (Floating Action Button)**: On Classes page — `fixed bottom-6 right-6 w-14 h-14 rounded-full bg-primary shadow-lg`
5. **Horizontal scroll**: For badge/tag lists — no wrapping
6. **Touch targets**: Minimum 44x44px for all interactive elements
7. **Safe area**: Account for notch/home indicator on mobile devices

### 5.3 Exam Mode Responsive

| Element | Mobile | Desktop |
|---|---|---|
| Question nav | Bottom drawer / sticky bottom bar | Left sidebar |
| Question display | Full width | Centered, max-w-2xl |
| Timer | Sticky top bar | Top right corner |
| Action buttons | Sticky bottom bar | Bottom right |

---

## 6. Accessibility Guidelines

### 6.1 Keyboard Navigation
- All interactive elements reachable via Tab in logical order
- Modal traps focus
- Escape key closes modals/dropdowns
- Arrow keys navigate within tabs, menus, radio groups (exam answers)

### 6.2 ARIA Patterns

| Component | ARIA Pattern |
|---|---|
| Modal | `role="dialog"`, `aria-modal="true"`, `aria-labelledby` |
| Dropdown menu | `role="menu"`, `role="menuitem"` |
| Tabs | `role="tablist"`, `role="tab"`, `aria-selected` |
| Exam question group | `role="radiogroup"` |
| Toast | `role="alert"`, `aria-live="polite"` |
| Progress bar | `role="progressbar"`, `aria-valuenow`, `aria-valuemin`, `aria-valuemax` |
| Loading | `aria-busy="true"`, `aria-label="Đang tải..."` |
| Badge status | `role="status"` |
| Exam timer | `aria-label="Thời gian còn lại"` |

### 6.3 Visual Accessibility
- Focus ring: `focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-primary focus-visible:ring-offset-2`
- Error messages: linked via `aria-describedby` to input
- Color is not the only indicator — icons and text always accompany status colors
- Minimum 4.5:1 contrast for body text

### 6.4 Exam-Specific Accessibility
- Timer announced to screen reader every minute: `aria-live="polite"` with time remaining
- Question numbers are `aria-label="Câu hỏi 1, đã trả lời"`
- Submit confirmation includes text summary, not just button

---

## 7. i18n Design

### 7.1 Translation Key Structure
```
nav.{page}           — Navigation labels
dashboard.welcome    — Welcome message
dashboard.stats.*    — Stat labels
page.{name}.title   — Page title
page.{name}.subtitle — Page subtitle
page.{name}.action.{action} — Action buttons
page.{name}.field.{field}   — Form labels
page.{name}.placeholder.{field} — Placeholder text
page.{name}.error.{error}    — Error messages
page.{name}.empty.title      — Empty state
page.{name}.empty.description — Empty description
status.*            — Status labels
exam.{action}       — Exam-specific actions
grade.*             — Grade-specific labels
common.*            — Common labels (save, cancel, etc.)
```

### 7.2 Language Switcher Design
```tsx
<div className="relative">
  <button
    className="flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-surface text-sm transition-colors"
    onClick={() => setOpen(!open)}
  >
    <span>{language === 'vi' ? '🇻🇳' : '🇺🇸'}</span>
    <span>{language === 'vi' ? 'Tiếng Việt' : 'English'}</span>
    <ChevronDown className="w-4 h-4" />
  </button>
</div>
```

### 7.3 RTL Consideration
- Currently not supported, but if needed: use `dir="rtl"` + `flex-row-reverse` pattern
- Icons that imply direction (arrows) should flip in RTL

